HOW FAR are “designer babies” from becoming a reality? Host Kenneth Cukier explores the ethical questions around the applications of a genome-wide association study. Journalist and author Gaia Vince explains how “cultural evolution” shapes society. And a solution to the problem of “concrete cancer”. Runtime: 23min Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/radiooffer    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn